item.title: Uzbekistan National News Agency
item.description: Launched in 1992, Uzbekistan National News Agency (UzA) is a state-affiliated news media and one of “the leading information agency of the country. UzA covers activities of the government agencies in the country, as well as socio-political events.

item.title: Xabar
item.description: Launched in 1992 by what is currently Ministry of Digital Technologies of the Republic of Uzbekistan, Xabar is a state-affiliated news media covering local and world affairs, technology, and sports.
